n essential sense, always opens up infinitude from the heart of finitude, to an irreducible outside of the profane order of worldly hegemonies. Religion here assumes a negative political theology of exception without sovereign power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPolitical theologyy19th century. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311078044440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474416917423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474416917/original  a978-3-11-078044-4  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK